how is cobalt-60 produced? Cobalt-60 is produced by bombarding natural uranium with neutrons. The resulting uranium-238 is then chemically separated and converted to cobalt-59. The cobalt-59 is then converted to cobalt-60 by bombarding it with neutrons. how is cobalt-60 used? Cobalt-60 is used to provide radiation for x-ray machines and industrial radiography, to sterilize food and medical supplies, and to treat cancer
